{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "The two leading candidates have pledged to break with Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg on a range of issues at the nexus of government and religion.", "abstract": "Bill de Blasio and Joseph J Lhota, two leading candidates for New York City mayor, have both pledged to make more concessions to religious groups than their predecessor Mayor Michael R Bloomberg; both would accommodate two of the most important Muslim holy days, allow church services on school property, and work with Jewish leaders to ease the city\u2019s supervision of circumcision rituals.", "section_name": "N.Y. / Region", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"lastname": "HERN\u00c1NDEZ", "rank": 1, "firstname": "Javier", "role": "reported", "organization": "", "middlename": "C."}], "original": "By JAVIER C. HERN\u00c1NDEZ", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/04/nyregion/top-2-candidates-vow-to-make-city-hall-more-faith-friendly.html", "lead_paragraph": "The two leading candidates have pledged to break with Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg on a range of issues at the nexus of government and religion.", "headline": {"main": "Top 2 Candidates Vow to Make City Hall More Faith-Friendly ", "print_headline": "Top 2 Candidates Vow to Make City Hall More Faith-Friendly"}, "_id": "5277173738f0d84d9ef64488", "word_count": "1329", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2013/11/04/nyregion/04faith-combo/04faith-combo-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2013/11/04/nyregion/04faith-combo/04faith-combo-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2013/11/04/nyregion/04faith-combo/04faith-combo-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2013/11/04/nyregion/04faith-combo/04faith-combo-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url